<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ920108-0161</DOCNO><DOCID>920108-0161.</DOCID><HL>   Canada Sees Fraud Risks   With Business in Nigeria</HL><DATE>01/08/92</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><IN>INTERNATIONAL TRADE NEWS (TRD)</IN><NS>TRADE ISSUES (TRD)</NS><RE>AFRICA (AF)CANADA (CN)NIGERIA (NI)NORTH AMERICA (NME)</RE><LP>   OTTAWA -- The Canadian government warned business peopleto be cautious in their Nigerian business dealings because offraud risks.   Illegal schemes in Nigeria include demands for unnecessarybusiness registration fees and scams involving visas,commercial samples and financial documents, Canadian TradeMinister Michael Wilson said.</LP><TEXT>   Mr. Wilson recommended that Canadian businesses enteringinto new relationships in Nigeria defer any trip to thecountry until Canadian officials in Lagos verify thecredentials of the Nigerians involved.   He said Nigeria's government is trying to combat thefraudulent activity.</TEXT></DOC>